Ask HN: Is There a Yelp for Software?
text:
Say I'm starting a new frontend project and I'm trying to decide whether to go with React or Vue. I might read some blogs or maybe search for a relevant discussion thread on here or Reddit, but what would be handy is having something like a Yelp for software.

I want something where I can get a quick feel for the software's current popularity and sentiment - say over the last year. I want to know what developers / users who rated it 5 stars think and what those who rated it 1 star think. I also want to read comments deemed most "useful" by the community.

Is there anything like this out there? I just realised I use services like TripAdvistor, Google Reviews and Trustpilot all the time when looking for traditional businesses, but I have no go to place when picking software.

Ask HN: Is notebook hardware getting worse?
text:
I've been using Lenovo ThinkPads for 13 years now and while I've been pretty happy with the Notebooks I've owned during the first of those years, I'm feeling like there have been more hardware issues during recent years:

- Fans are becoming noisier

- Keyboards are becoming worse

- Docking Stations have more issues (not charging via USB-C/Thunderbolt, external displays not being detected, ...)

I've also heard about similar problems with MacBooks from colleagues.

Is this just my subjective experience or do you also see degrading quality with your hardware?

Show HN: I wrote a book on Site Reliability Engineering
text:
Hello Everyone! I finally published Site Reliability Engineering Tidbits on leanpub.

https://leanpub.com/sretidbits

This book is a collection of 28 chapters on SRE concepts such as observability, monitoring, Service Level Objectives (SLOs), alerting, resilience and debugging.

This book aims to provide hands on examples of implementing a number of concepts described in Google's SRE books. It also describes how i've seen SRE concepts impact some of the organizations I've worked in.

I previously announced this book here, but it was not on leanpub yet:

https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=30064570

Thank you for looking and I appreciate your feedback!
